surf_froots2

Tier 4-5, 20 stages, 5 bonuses

Made by a collection of mappers nearly a year ago. Progress dropped as soon as the deadline hit in January 2019. 7 months after that, I took over using the files I had in order to uphold the promise made to the mappers that their work would be released.

This work is released with the permission of Krazy (the lead host).

Lastly, I'd like to say sorry to the people who's work didn't actually make it. The LSD bonus made by 111112oo had to be removed due to genuine safety concerns and iNooVa made a stage which didn't make it due to late submission and the map being at 96% limits.

Thank you to everyone who participated and worked on this. On behalf of the hosts; sorry it took so long.

If you would like to port this to CS:GO/TF2, add me on Discord (pretzL#0001) and I'll give you the files.

In my opinion most of the surf is tier 3 with a few tricky parts but the stages are very long. Bonus is probably tier 2; teleport to bonus is located at stage 1 start.

try r_3dsky 0. 
Most of the wall lights are illusionary (you can go through them)
There are a lot of landmarks in the map. Playing with high ping will reduce gameplay quality

My first surf Map.

Development of this started about ~5 years ago, but then I forgot about it after a few months...

Now I have taken the time to make something of it.

It consists of 3 stages and 2 bonuses. Difficulty wise i feel that it is somewhere between Tier2 and Tier3. The bonuses are ~Tier4

Evo Update (Thanks to feedback from Granis):
* Use Landmark Angles on trigger_teleports
* Teleporters on the bonuses no longer allow the players to keep their speed
* Adapted the surf angle on ramps where the layout allowed it without destroying the original feeling of the map (might lower difficulty slightly)
* Optimized skybox and void facing textures
* Changed Bonus2 to ordinary gravity (might increase difficulty slightly)
* Players no longer take fall damage

Evo2 Update
* Re-worked the map visually, using different textures for over- and underground areas
* Improved lighting
* Improved player experience for some teleporters
* Removed annoying sounds
* Improved the surf a little bit
* Added bonus3
* Added Counter-Strike:Source version

The Evo2 update is hopefully the last change I make to this map.

It should feel better to play now, as well as also being available for CSS.

Being my first map, I learned from this as much as I could and I am now looking forward to bigger and better Projects :)

IMPORTANT FOR SERVEROWNERS:
If you have a timer which hooks to trigger_multiples, do not use this for any of the startzones. It seems hooking to zones somehow removes the trigger‚Äôs outputs, which breaks the entire map‚Äôs filtersystem. Instead, zone these manually or atleast doublecheck it doesn‚Äôt completely fuck everything. Alternatively use Stripper to duplicate the startzones and then hook to them.

= Surf_Chasm by Sid =

This map has been in the works for a while, and I'm very happy that I committed to the project. The final result is a fantastic map and I'm very proud to release Surf_Chasm!

Set inside a large earthquake split, an industrial company saw profit in a liquid that had been exposed. What did they find? Why did they abandon the project? Why does a surf map need a plot? These questions are not for me to answer. All I know is the obstacles and sights of Chasm will have you coming back for more.
